The paper analyzes metadata associated with web videos, which involves aspects of multimedia (MM) such as video formats, resolutions, and durations. The analysis also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques to extract and process the metadata. The paper discusses the properties of web video, which can be relevant to social media (SI) and digital libraries (DL). Finally, the paper touches upon issues related to content recognition (CR) and copyright, which are also relevant to web video.
